The Entra (Azure AD) client secret for the reimbursements mailbox app expires on
<%= @expires_on.to_fs(:rfc822) %> — <%= @days_left %> days from now.

When it expires, receipt emails to the reimbursements mailbox stop being processed
and replies stop being sent.

To rotate it:
1. entra.microsoft.com -> App registrations -> "BlackLightning Reimbursements Mailbox"
   -> Certificates & secrets -> New client secret.
2. Update the azure_client_secret (and azure_secret_expires_on) in the Rails
   production credentials, and the fnox/Bitwarden entry for development.
3. Redeploy.

This warning repeats daily until the recorded expiry date is updated.
